<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: BRITISH COMPANY TO PAY $15 MILLION FOR ANDUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Courtaulds, a British chemical, textile and industrial products company, has 
agreed to buy Andus Corp. in Canoga Park from its parent company, Raychem Corp. 
of Palo Alto. 
</P>
<P>
Courtaulds will pay $15 million. As much as $10 million more may be paid to 
Raychem should Andus' revenue growth meet certain targets. 
</P>
