<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: FLAMEMASTER REPORTS GAIN IN INCOME, LOSS IN REVENUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flamemaster Corp. reported net income of $135,000, or 11 cents a share, for the 
fourth quarter that ended Sept. 30, compared to $120,000, or 10 cents a share, 
in the same period the year before. Revenue fell 31% to $1.1 million compared 
to $1.6 million in the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The Sun Valley-based company makes flame-retardant coatings and sealants. 
</P>
<P>
For the fiscal year that ended Sept. 30, Flamemaster posted a profit of 
$438,000, or 28 cents a share, compared to $443,000, or 28 cents a share, a 
year earlier. Revenue was down 13% to $5.1 million from $5.8 million the year 
before. 
