<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: PROGRAM SUCCESSFUL FOR HEALTH STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton has announced that for the second year in a row, 100% of 
its Health Professions Program students who applied to professional schools 
were accepted. The applicants were students seeking admittance to medical, 
dental or other health-related schools. 
</P>
<P>
Miles D. McCarthy, emeritus professor of biology and coordinator of the Health 
Professions Program, said Cal State Fullerton's work in preparing students for 
advanced health-care study has gained a very favorable national reputation. 
</P>
<P>
He said the university had been moving up in recent years in the percentage of 
students accepted for professional schools, culminating in the past 2 years 
with 100% acceptances. "Since 1980, the acceptance rate has climbed above the 
85% mark every year but one and has passed the 90% mark four times," McCarthy 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
