<HEADLINE>
<P>
VERY SUBTLE WINS LAS FLORES HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Very Subtle pulled away in the stretch to win the $70,600 Las Flores Handicap 
by 3 lengths over Sadie B. Fast before a crowd of 29,001 Monday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Laffit Pincay and carrying high weight of 124 pounds, Very Subtle 
covered 6 furlongs in 1:08 3-5 and paid $2.60 to win. 
</P>
<P>
Sadie B. Fast, ridden by Bill Shoemaker and carrying 113 pounds, was 3 1/2 
lengths ahead of Comical Cat at the wire. 
</P>
<P>
The $5 exacta of Very Subtle and Sadie B. Fast paid $18. Serve N' Volley was 
scratched. Because there were only three entries in the 37th running of the 
race for older fillies and mares, there was no place or show wagering. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the 12th in 26 starts for Very Subtle, a 5-year-old daughter of 
Hoist the Silver, and the $44,350 top prize increased her career earnings to 
$1,560,860. 
</P>
</TEXT>
