<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
NORTH'S LAWYERS SUBPEONA SHULTZ, OTHER OFFICIALS IN IRAN-CONTRA CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lawyers for former White House aide Oliver L. North have issued subpoenas for 
Secretary of State George P. Shultz and other top State Department officials to 
testify in the trial arising from the Iran-Contra affair, the State Department 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
President Reagan and President-elect George Bush have already been served with 
similar subpoenas. Their aides have indicated that they would refuse to testify 
on constitutional grounds. 
</P>
<P>
State Department spokeswoman Phyllis Oakley said Shultz would appear if that 
were deemed necessary "by the parties and the court." She said other State 
officials subpoenaed included Elliott Abrams, assistant secretary for 
inter-American affairs; Michael Armacost, undersecretary for political affairs; 
Charles Hill, Shultz's executive assistant, and department legal adviser 
Abraham Soafer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
