<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSING WOMAN'S BODY FOUND IN FREEZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By UPI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CANTON, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a school administrator's wife who was reported missing more than 
three years ago was found by her daughter in a freezer in the basement of the 
family home, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Police were holding a suspect in the death of Dorothy Tyburski but they 
declined to identify the suspect or speculate about possible causes of her 
death. Tyburski's husband, Leonard, is dean of students at Mackenzie High 
School in Detroit. A neighbor said Leonard Tyburski had told him that his wife 
had left him and moved to Ohio. 
</P>
</TEXT>
