<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
SPEEDING DRIVER HITS POLE, IS KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Huntington Beach man, who police said was driving his Chevrolet Corvette at 
106 m.p.h., died Monday night when he lost control of the car and hit a power 
pole on Bolsa Chica Road, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Frank Rossi, 26, was driving southbound on Bolsa Chica Road near Westminster 
Boulevard about 9:15 p.m. Monday when Westminster Police Officer J. Davidson, 
using radar, determined he was traveling 106 m.p.h., Lt. Richard Main said. 
</P>
<P>
Davidson said he attempted to catch up to the driver and pull him over, but 
Rossi went out of control just north of Rancho Road and slammed into a power 
pole. 
</P>
<P>
"The driver was ejected on impact and landed in the flood control channel," 
Main said. 
</P>
<P>
Rossi died later at Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center, he 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
